## Second-pass done: `src/blog/people/drafts/Alex-Warren.md`

The fresh-eyes review was sharp and mostly correct. I researched the two real gaps, then made targeted changes.

**Main things I changed:**

- **Filled the pre-music black hole.** The industry-plant section now opens on who Alex actually *was* — co-founded and named Hype House, 600k+ YouTube subs of first-person prank videos, "the class clown in a house full of clowns." This makes the goofball-to-gospel-balladeer whiplash visible instead of asserted, and lets the lighter Alex exist so the insecurity lands by contrast (fixes the "monochrome sad-boy" note too).
- **Added the music.** After the Yaron quote, a new beat describes what "Ordinary" actually sounds like (acoustic confession detonating into a gospel choir) and places him in the Teddy Swims / Benson Boone earnest-big-voice wave. It sits where the manufactured-vs-real question already lives.
- **Gave Kouvr a real beat.** Expanded from a fragment to the full arc: met on Snapchat when he was a nobody, moved into his car, and their wedding was officiated by the man who took them off the street. Now it's genuine growth-arrow proof, and it pays off the intro's "song about staying."
- **Earned the faith claim** with one concrete beat — raised Catholic, years furious at God, faith as how he keeps his dead parents in the room — tied to the Type 3 twist (worship as the one performance with no scoreboard).
- **Trimmed the repetition.** Cut the literal "ten weeks at No. 1" echo in the middle section, relocated the key-stat box out of the empathy turn to the chart material, trimmed its UK line so that stat only lands once (in the closing), and softened the third "verdict" so the "standing over a sink" image stays the strong one.

**Left untouched** (review said don't): the Ferrari/"See you tomorrow, Dad" closing, the empathy-turn sentence, and the industry-plant collapse shape.

**Still open:** "Bloodline" is named but not described sonically — I kept the artistry beat focused on "Ordinary" rather than sprawling into a discography. An editor pass could add one line if you want the music thread heavier. That's the only thing I'd flag for a possible editor pass.

Sources used for the research: [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alex_Warren), [Sound on Sound – Inside Track: "Ordinary"](https://www.soundonsound.com/techniques/inside-track-alex-warren-ordinary), [Today – Kouvr Annon](https://www.today.com/popculture/alex-warren-wife-kovur-annon-relationship-rcna256544), [Slate on the earnest-male-vocalist wave](https://slate.com/culture/2025/06/alex-warren-ordinary-billboard-hot-100-teddy-swims.html), [Variety-sourced faith quotes via Jubilee](http://www.jubileecast.com/articles/34381/20260129/alex-warren-opens-up-about-faith-grief-and-the-spiritual-undercurrent-shaping-his-music.htm).
